  <section refnum="1" xml:id="S1">
    <title><tag close=" ">1</tag>Basics</title>
    <para xml:id="S1.p1">
      <p framecolor="#000000" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt" framed="rectangle">This is stuff that’s framed.</p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S1.p2">
      <p>Note that the</p>
      <p framecolor="#000000" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt" framed="rectangle">framed</p>
      <p>stuff is a block!</p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S1.p3">
      <inline-block cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt" framecolor="#000000" framed="rectangle">
        <p>This is stuff that’s framed.</p>
        <p>And it can hold multiple paragraphs.</p>
      </inline-block>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S1.p4">
      <p framecolor="#000000" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt" framed="rectangle">And even stuff in multiple Paragraphs.</p>
    </para>
    <paragraph xml:id="S1.SS0.SSS0.P1">
      <title>Does this work?</title>
      <para xml:id="S1.SS0.SSS0.P1.p1">
        <p>But not in LaTeXML!</p>
      </para>
    </paragraph>
  </section>
  <section refnum="2" xml:id="S2">
    <title><tag close=" ">2</tag>Variants</title>
    <para xml:id="S2.p1">
      <p framecolor="#000000" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt" framed="rectangle">This is stuff that’s framed, but would stay open at page breaks.
This doesn’t make so much sense for LaTeXML, so it’s pretty much
the same.</p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S2.p2">
      <p backgroundcolor="#80BF80" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt">
        <text backgroundcolor="#80BF80">This is stuff that’s shaded green;
should fade into the margin, whatever that means.</text>
      </p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S2.p3">
      <p backgroundcolor="#80BF80" cssstyle="padding-top:12pt;padding-bottom:12pt">
        <text backgroundcolor="#80BF80">This is stuff that’s shaded green;
it should end sharply at the margin.</text>
      </p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S2.p4">
      <p backgroundcolor="#80BF80" cssstyle="padding-top:3pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
        <text backgroundcolor="#80BF80">This is stuff that’s snugly shaded green;
fading into the margin.</text>
      </p>
    </para>
    <para xml:id="S2.p5">
      <p backgroundcolor="#80BF80" cssstyle="padding-top:3pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
